GDP In Chained (2015) Dollars -> Goods Producing Industries -> Other Goods Industries (Million Dollars):
Other goods industries comprise agriculture, fishing and quarrying.

Aggregate value of the goods and services produced in the economic territory of Singapore. The GDP estimates are compiled based on the output (or production), expenditure and income approaches. See Output-based GDP, Expenditure-based GDP and Income-based GDP.

Gross value added is derived by the output or income approach. 
The output approach measures value added as output less intermediate consumption.  Output refers to the value of goods and services produced  while intermediate consumption is value of goods and services consumed as inputs by a process of production, e.g. materials, utilities, fuel, rental paid for premises and equipment, banking and financial charges and other operating costs.
The income approach derives value added as the sum of incomes generated from the domestic production of goods and services, which comprise gross operating surplus, remuneration and taxes (less subsidies) on production.
na   not available or not applicable
-     nil or negligible or not significant
Numbers may not add up to the totals due to rounding.
Data are the latest available at the time of access or download. Some statistics, particularly those for the most recent time periods, are provisional and may be subject to revision at a later date.
Values are shown in Singapore dollars (unless otherwise specified)
